data.chText: （为达到某一目标的）过程；进程
data.enText: a series of things that are done in order to achieve a particular result

data.chText: 磋商过程
data.enText: a consultation process

data.chText: 开始进行教育制度改革的艰难历程
data.enText: to begin the difficult process of reforming the education system

data.chText: 做任何改革恐怕都会是个缓慢的过程。
data.enText: I'm afraid getting things changed will be a slow process.

data.chText: 思维过程
data.enText: mental processes

data.chText: 戒毒对他是个漫长、痛苦的过程。
data.enText: Coming off the drug was a long and painful (= difficult) process for him.

data.chText: 用排除法找出你对哪种食物过敏。
data.enText: Find which food you are allergic to by a process of elimination .

data.chText: 我们正在出售自家的住宅。
data.enText: We're in the process of selling our house.

data.chText: 我在挪动家具时崴了脚。
data.enText: I was moving some furniture and I twisted my ankle in the process (= while I was doing it) .

data.chText: （事物发展，尤指自然变化的）过程，步骤，流程
data.enText: a series of things that happen, especially ones that result in natural changes

data.chText: 老化过程
data.enText: the ageing process

data.chText: 那是学习过程中的正常现象。
data.enText: It's a normal part of the learning process .

data.chText: 做事方法；工艺流程；工序
data.enText: a method of doing or making sth, especially one that is used in industry

data.chText: 制造方法
data.enText: manufacturing processes

data.chText: 加工；处理
data.enText: to treat raw material, food, etc. in order to change it, preserve it, etc.

data.chText: 我们买的大部分食品都用某种方法加工过。
data.enText: Most of the food we buy is processed in some way.

data.chText: 加工好的干酪
data.enText: processed cheese

data.chText: 我送了三个胶卷去冲印。
data.enText: I sent three rolls of film away to be processed.

data.chText: 污水处理厂
data.enText: a sewage processing plant

data.chText: 审阅，审核，处理（文件、请求等）
data.enText: to deal officially with a document, request, etc.

data.chText: 审核你的申请需要一周时间。
data.enText: It will take a week for your application to be processed.

data.chText: 数据处理
data.enText: to perform a series of operations on data in a computer

data.chText: 食品加工业
data.enText: the food processing industry

data.chText: 列队行进；缓缓前进
data.enText: to walk or move along slowly in, or as if in, a procession

simple_means.memory_skill: pro 向前 + cess 行走，前进 → 向前走的〔历程〕→ 过程

means: (事物发展，尤指自然变化的)步骤

tr: a sustained phenomenon or one marked by gradual changes through a series of states
example: the process of calcification begins later for boys than for girls

tr: a particular course of action intended to achieve a result
example: the procedure of obtaining a driver's license
it was a process of trial and error

tr: a natural prolongation or projection from a part of an organism either animal or plant
(psychology) the performance of some composite cognitive activity
an operation that affects mental contents
a mental process that you are not directly aware of
a writ issued by authority of law
usually compels the defendant's attendance in a civil suit
failure to appear results in a default judgment against the defendant
subject to a process or treatment, with the aim of readying for some purpose, improving, or remedying a condition
example: treat the water so it can be drunk

tr: perform mathematical and logical operations on (data) according to programmed instructions in order to obtain the required information
example: The results of the elections were still being processed when he gave his acceptance speech

tr: deliver a warrant or summons to someone
example: He was processed by the sheriff

tr: shape, form, or improve a material

example: They processed into the dining room

tr: deal with in a routine way

example: He was warned that the district attorney would process him
She actioned the company for discrimination

value.def: A process is a series of actions which are carried out in order to achieve a particular result.

example.ex: There was total agreement to start the peace process as soon as possible...
example.tran: 全体一致同意尽快开始和平进程。

example.ex: They decided to spread the building process over three years...
example.tran: 他们决定用3年时间建成。

example.ex: The best way to proceed is by a process of elimination.
example.tran: 继续进行下去的最佳方式是实行淘汰制。

value.def: A process is a series of things which happen naturally and result in a biological or chemical change.

example.ex: It occurs in elderly men, apparently as part of the ageing process...
example.tran: 这种情况出现在老年人当中，显然是衰老过程的一部分。

example.ex: The regularity with which this occurs suggests that the process is genetically determined.
example.tran: 这种现象出现的规律性表明这个过程是由基因决定的。

value.def: When raw materials or foods are processed, they are prepared in factories before they are used or sold.

example.ex: ...fish which are processed by freezing, canning or smoking...
example.tran: 经过冷冻、罐装或熏制处理的鱼

example.ex: The material will be processed into plastic pellets.
example.tran: 这些材料将会被加工成塑料小球。

example.ex: ...diets high in refined and processed foods.
example.tran: 包含很多精制食品和加工食品的饮食

example.ex: ...the cost of re-engineering the production process.
example.tran: 重新设计生产过程的成本

example.ex: America sent cotton to England for processing.
example.tran: 美国把棉花运到英格兰进行加工。

example.ex: ...nuclear fuel processing plant.
example.tran: 核燃料处理厂

value.def: When people process information, they put it through a system or into a computer in order to deal with it.

example.ex: ...facilities to process the data, and the right to publish the results...
example.tran: 处理数据的设备和公开其结果的权利

example.ex: The information gathered by the telescopes will be processed by computers.
example.tran: 通过望远镜获得的信息将由计算机进行处理。

example.ex: ...data processing...
example.tran: 数据处理

example.ex: The advances in communications altered the nature of information processing.
example.tran: 通讯技术的进步使信息处理发生了质的改变。

value.def: When people are processed by officials, their case is dealt with in stages and they pass from one stage of the process to the next.

example.ex: Patients took more than two hours to be processed through the department.
example.tran: 病人在这个科看病需要两个多小时的时间。

value.tran: 审核；审议；检查；使接受处理

value.def: If you are in the process of doing something, you have started to do it and are still doing it.

example.ex: The administration is in the process of drawing up a peace plan...
example.tran: 政府正在起草和平计划。

example.ex: Her novel is in the process of being turned into a television series.
example.tran: 她的小说正被拍成电视连续剧。

value.def: If you are doing something and you do something else in the process, you do the second thing as part of doing the first thing.

example.ex: He finished ahead of the Spaniard, and in the process picked up his first time trial win as a pro...
example.tran: 他领先那个西班牙人到达终点，同时也首次作为职业选手获得计时赛的胜利。

example.ex: You have to let us struggle for ourselves, even if we must die in the process.
example.tran: 你得让我们为自己拼搏，哪怕我们会在这个过程中死去。

rootsaffixes.indicate: = to go, to proceed 行走, 前进
rootsaffixes.title: ced, ceed, cess

partsOfSpeech.dec: ac 加强 + ced 行走，前进 + e → 一起走 → 同意
ac 加强 + cess 行走，前进 → 一再向前走 → 接近
an 加强 + cest〔= cess〕行走，前进 + or 表人 → 走了很久的人 → 祖先
ante 前面 + ced 行走，前进 + ent 具有…性质的，关于…的 → 先行的；以前的
ced 行走，前进 + e →〔使〕走开 → 割让
ex 出 + ceed 行走，前进 → 走出去 → 超越
inter 在…之间 + ced 行走，前进 + e → 在两者中间走 → 调停
pre 预先 + ced 行走，前进 + e → 在先，优于
pre 前；预先 + ced 行走，前进 + ent 表名词 → 在前面的东西 → 先例
pro 在前 + ced 行走，前进 + ure 表结果 → 前面经过的〔历程〕→ 程序
pro 向前 + ceed 行走，前进 → 继续进行，前进
pro 向前 + cess 行走，前进 → 向前走的〔历程〕→ 过程
process 过程；进行 + ion 表名词 → 向前走 → 队伍
re 向后 + ced 行走，前进 + e → 后退
re 回 + cess 行走，前进 → 走回去 → 休息
recess 休息；暂停 + ion 表动作 → 走回去 → 撤退
se 分开 + ced 行走，前进 + e → 分开走 → 脱离
suc 下 + ceed 行走，前进 → 从下面走到上面 → 成功
suc 下 + cess 行走，前进 → 成功，胜利
un 无 + precedent 前例 + ed 表形容词 → 史无前例的
